
# Credit Risk Prediction Walkthrough

This notebook demonstrates a full ML workflow on a credit-risk dataset using scikit-learn.

1️⃣ **Load data**
```python
import pandas as pd, seaborn as sns, matplotlib.pyplot as plt
df = pd.read_csv("../data/credit_risk.csv")
df.head()
```

2️⃣ **EDA**
```python
sns.pairplot(df, hue="default")
sns.heatmap(df.corr(), annot=True, cmap="coolwarm")
```

3️⃣ **Model training**
```python
from src.features import build_preprocessor
from src.models import model_candidates
from sklearn.pipeline import Pipeline

X = df.drop(columns=["default"])
y = df["default"]
pre = build_preprocessor(X)
model = model_candidates()
pipe = Pipeline([("pre", pre), ("model", model)])
pipe.fit(X, y)
```

4️⃣ **Evaluation**
```python
from sklearn.metrics import roc_curve, auc, classification_report
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
y_pred = pipe.predict(X)
print(classification_report(y, y_pred))
fpr, tpr, _ = roc_curve(y, pipe.predict_proba(X)[:,1])
plt.plot(fpr, tpr)
plt.title(f"ROC AUC={auc(fpr,tpr):.2f}")
plt.savefig("../reports/roc_curve.png")
```

5️⃣ **Explainability**
```python
import shap
shap.initjs()
explainer = shap.Explainer(pipe.named_steps["model"], feature_names=pipe.named_steps["pre"].get_feature_names_out())
X_trans = pipe.named_steps["pre"].transform(X)
shap_values = explainer(X_trans)
shap.summary_plot(shap_values, X_trans, show=False)
plt.savefig("../reports/shap_summary.png", bbox_inches="tight")
```

6️⃣ **Save model**
```python
from joblib import dump
dump(pipe, "../models/credit_risk.joblib")
```
